nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uevryl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evryl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 10:06:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Well I've hit 193 Int and have quite a few slots open still. Should I go for more int or more charisma? Should I sacrifice a few points of int for a charisma boost? Or should I just wait till I have Charisma boosting spells? Right now my Charisma is at 100.<br>
<br>
Any advice? <p>Evryl <br>
Ranger of the 23th Fletching<br>Wood Elf Servant of Tunare 
<br><br>
Eline<br>
Enchantress of the 13 Mezzing<br>Agnostic Member of Whatever Race I Happen to Be At the Moment.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unandiinumezzina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandiinu Mezzina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 1:09:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> I would choose charisma over int beacuse later on &quot;I&quot; think that charisma does have a effect on how often a (insert some form of mesmerize) or (insert some form of charm) sticks or in the case of the charm how long it lasts.  I went with Dark Elf as my class (at the time i did not know CHA was so important) but right now when buffed i have 167 CHA and 182 int.  So i would go for cha.  Some cheap +CHA like the golden cat's eye agate bracers (+7 Cha), Opaline Earrings (+5 cha), Crude Stein (+15 CHA).  Well I hoped this helps.  If you need help I will be glad to answer your questions to the best of my knowledge.  If I could not help you I bet LLorian (who i can bet will be making a post on this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) will be glad to help you.<br>
<br>
Nandiinu Mezzina<br>
Lvl 39 Enchanter (I need to make a sig <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Member of Soldiers of the Flame <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukalandra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalandra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 3:46:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Get cha to at least 140 buffed, but again, the higher the better.  Don't need to get int above 200 at all, and really, what you have right now should stand you in good steed (have 186 buffed myself at 44 and I hardly ever go OOM, even when speeding up 5 people).<br>
<br>
Kalandra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udaeon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 4:42:34 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/hamster2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> I wish I had Cha at 100 at level 13.. =/  Was around 80-something.. heh...  Int waas uh.. prolly 125 or so =P<br>
<br>
In any case, I really don't think you need to worry about CHA till you start to get into your 30s - that's when you'll be really getting down into the crowd control-type stuff.<br>
<br>
However, with Int that high, certainly can't hurt to start working on cha gear now.. this way you'll get a head start on AC/HP/Mana gear once that really starts to count (which uh.. is always.. heh.. but really only surfaces in higher levels) <p><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
54th Illusionist<b> - <a href = http://www.eternalsinn.org>Eternal Sinn</a></b><br>
<i>High Council Member</i> and 
<i>Public Relations Rep</i><br></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udaeon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0> at: 8/5/01 4:43:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uerrtai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errtai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 5:06:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> My order of preferences for stats go like this<br>
<br>
1. Hitpoints/STA<br>
2. Int/mana<br>
3. AC/AGI<br>
4. Charisma<br>
<br>
Myself and other have done lots of tests mezzing and charming with high CHA versus low CHA, the difference is negligible.<br>
<br>
I would say landing a mez depends 75% on your level, 20% on the mob's magic resistance, and 5% on your CHA.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 7:27:54 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> My suggestion would be to :<br>
<br>
Get your int to 190 + ( buffed, since you can always count on your own personal buffs )<br>
<br>
Up your Hit points , and Armor class.<br>
<br>
Get your Charisma to  170+ buffed <br>
<br>
In that order.  <br>
<br>
I am not going to debate charisma , because it is one of the most touchy subjects we have.  I CAN tell you, with my own personal observation, i mezz just the same naked as i do clothed (resist rate).  The only differences i have naked are :<br>
<br>
Lack of mana ( +int )<br>
Lack of HP<br>
Lack of AC<br>
<br>
With that being said, &quot;my&quot; personal goal was to have good HP / AC, while still maintaining 200+ int (buffed) , and 190 + cha (buffed).  I currently have 1815 HP self buffed, with 212 int and 202 cha self buffed ( and like 700 ac i believe).<br>
<br>
My personal choice has been to go more for HP than AC, but others make slightly different choices.  Our gear doesnt make so much difference in what we do that it matters much anyhow <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A> at: 8/6/01 7:45:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uultravoices.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ultravoices</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 9:02:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> <tt>I have lots of CHA items, and not a lot of INT items. I seldom note a problem with mana. My resists in everything but MR are so-so, but I find MR to be vital for many reasons, not the least of which is not mezzing yourself in an AOE mez situation when the quarters are tight. My MR is 90 buffed if I'm wearing my Advisor robe, and I can hardly effect myself with magic based spells.<br>
<br>
My gear isn't very good, really, because I've yet to go to planes or go to places were desirable caster gear drops in a while... and for the most part, I've earned or bought every single piece of gear that I have. The main cha items that I have on at the moment are:<br>
<br>
velium star ruby veil (( thank you Ravno ))<br>
2 electrum star ruby rings (( thank you gnarlimon ))<br>
2 golden cat's eye bracelets (( thank you ranger who was camping the mino hero back when I was a baby gnome back in steamfont, and thank you gnarlimon for replacing them when I gave them to a guild chanter to help them out ))<br>
incandescent gloves<br>
drake hide leggings<br>
crude stein<br>
split paw tooth necklace<br>
<br>
Except for the veil, the other items are cheap and/or fun to aquire.<br>
<br>
I swapped out the rod of insidious glamour for a stein of moggok, and int is around 166 with buff, and cha around 175 with buff (( more if a shaman drops Charisma on me, Glamour is only 2-odd points more than my current buff )), depending on if I swap in or out some of the int and cha items that I have in the bank.<br>
<br>
Does CHA help a lot? Maybe so, maybe no. Level is a much more imporant factor, I would say. But, one needs every edge that you can get, seeing as resists tend to be more fatal to us as a class...<br>
<br>
I plan on improving my resists more in the near future, more than I plan on improving my CHA or INT.</tt><br>
 <p><BR>
Olenari - Enchanter of the 46th Illusion - [Knights of the Flame] - Lanys<BR>
Eorot Floaat - Druid of the 30th Season - Lanys<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uphanttasm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phant Tasm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/5/01 11:56:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Find your deaths are caused by you running out of mana? Get more int/mana<br>
Find your deaths are caused by you running out of health? Get more ac/sta<br>
Find your deaths are caused by repeated resists? Get more cha<br>
<br>
I keep my cha over 200, and go with hp/sta/agi/ac <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=40078"><img BORDER="0" SRC="http://members.aol.com/raintalos/sig.gif"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ualundraadjani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlundraAdjani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/6/01 12:31:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://alundraadjani.com/otherstuff/eq/catface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Hmm, all of my deaths ARE caused when I run out of health, yours aren't? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyhow, I am one of the chanters who (deluded or not) seems to notice a difference between mezzing naked and clothed, or when I forget to refresh my cha buff, so I think cha matters more than 5%, but I also haven't done any analytical tests. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Just know that there's disagreement over how much it really matters. <p><img src="http://www.annastazia.homestead.com/files/adjani.jpg" alt="Adjani Tristesse, Goddess of Lanys"></img>
<br>
59th Saucy Beguiler
<br>
Guildleader of <a href="http://www.theroyalknights.org"> The Royal Knights </a><br>
Signature courtesy of Annastazia ;)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwyndalmisteltan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyndal Misteltan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/6/01 3:37:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Having just completed my Insidious Rod quest I can now, finally, get my CHA to 200 self-buffed. Does it make a difference *shrug*, but its nice to have. My INT is only 176 self-buffed with this equipment set (roll on Brilliance), but I've never found it a problem. Swap in your INT gear at the start of a session, then swap in the CHA after you start draining mana. I don't think I've ever managed to get back to full mana during a session, even with only 176 INT, there is usually always someone to buff, a Mob to slow or mez, etc.  My point is that if you never get to full mana, there is no point having more INT (apart from skill increases, hehe).<br>
<br>
Get several sets of items (INT/mana/AC/Hp/CHA/MR) and get used to swapping them in and out depending on the circumstances.  However, my main advice to you, is to get your MR to 100 self-buffed, if you can.  This seems to be the magic number for Mesmerisation, ie. the MR at which you infrequently mez yourself. I love single-target mez, but this spell is the life-saver when you're over-run, get MR to 100 and you won't stand there looking stupid as your party gets ripped apart <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
Kaldon Fallenstar, 42nd Season Enchanter<br>
Heroes of The Old Lands <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uistrahdamtheland.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Istrahd Amtheland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Buffy Bait</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/6/01 4:54:30 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/istrahd/lurker.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Phant - I know what you meant - but gah - I think Adj got you on that one /snicker. <p><TABLE ALIGN="center" BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH="425">

