<p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=2156">58 Chanter</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umukhtaribnasim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukhtar Ibn Asim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/6/01 7:27:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Int or Charisma?</span><hr size=1> Personally I think the level of CHA you need is partially dependent on what type of hunting you do.<br>
<br>
When taking down loads and loads of blue mobs I would tend to agree with Llorian.  CHA really doesn't make that much difference.  However when you go into areas where most of the mobs con yellow or higher to you, suddenly I notice a much greater difference in my successes mezzing, debuffing, etc between when I have gear and when I'm doing naked CR's.  As I personally vastly prefer fighting red mobs to blue ones (bragging rights ya know) I try and keep my CHA over 200 if I can and only let it drop below this when swapping in the resist gear for dragons... or when I am the primary haste buffer (Gah... must... get... shissar!) on a large, melee heavy raid and I really need the mana to keep everyone running at maximum efficiency and probably won't be doing much mezzing.<br>
<br>
